Classifications change as we learn more about the evolution of species, but as it stands, birds are officially dinosaurs, which personally I think is pretty cool :)

@Stephen
@Jon

I fully acknowledge that you guys are 100% correct.  Birds are the living descendants of the dinosaurs, at least according to our ability to know such things.

And I love that we remind people of this startling fact.  It's astonishing and fascinating that the dinosaur remnants are birds.  

I wonder what humble species will be the remnants of humans.

@Francis

This is one of my favorite facts. There's no "probably" about it. Some of the most well-known dinosaurs, like velociraptors, were covered in feathers and resembled birds. Even T-Rex is in the theropod group from which birds descended. When I observe especially large birds, like the herons at the creek near my house, it doesn't seem like a stretch at all. 

/www.birdlife.org/news/2021/12/21/its-official-birds-are-literally-dinosaurs-heres-how-we-know/

