You inspired me to think if I have a personal hero. I don't think I've ever considered this before. Apparently I don't 🤷. It may be related to my not abiding rites and rituals, and being wary of modern myths (over here they are often used to obscure history for dramatic effect, sometimes for political goals). I understand symbols as elements of art or oratory, but I don't need any in my life. I take lessons from life and history, but literal ones. Having a hero involves mythologizing them, I think, and once a person becomes a myth I lose interest in them, maybe because I suspect truth is lost in the process?

